562,0.02586922,0.1543033,0.00177481,-0.02293836,0.01113626,-0.0196873,0.00274583,0.00449314,0.02070827,0.01156595,0.03947052,0.14241794,-0.01686613,0.035733,0.08822341,-0.08154844,-0.04535265,-0.00620935,-0.01679726,0.0349922,-0.02015495,-0.06351835,-0.04427311,0.10844706,-0.04920028,-0.01710901,-0.03320826,-0.02531916,-0.02451006,-0.01902662,0.00793126,0.0233079,0.05890926,-0.02365317,-0.04337913,-0.01687769,-0.00441204,-0.05757975,-0.0466359,-0.00959198,0.02683123,-0.06552371,0.09911431,-0.01698823],"last_embed":{"hash":"1q3wwyr","tokens":422}}},"last_read":{"hash":"1q3wwyr","at":1774951889571},"class_name":"SmartSource","last_import":{"mtime":1774951820747,"size":2331,"at":1774951884799,"hash":"1q3wwyr"},"blocks":{"#---frontmatter---":[1,41],"#A review of the effects of mushrooms on mood and neurocognitive health across the lifespan.":[43,47],"#A review of the effects of mushrooms on mood and neurocognitive health across the lifespan.#{1}":[45,47]},"outlinks":[{"title":"Author/S. Cha","target":"Author/S. Cha","line":33},{"title":"Author/L. Bell","target":"Author/L. Bell","line":34},{"title":"Author/B. Shukitt-Hale","target":"Author/B. Shukitt-Hale","line":35},{"title":"Author/C. M. Williams","target":"Author/C. M. Williams","line":36},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/cha_review_2024/cha_review_2024.pdf","line":38}],"metadata":{"id":"cha_review_2024","type":"article-journal","title":"A review of the effects of mushrooms on mood and neurocognitive health across the lifespan.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2024]]},"DOI":"10.1016/j.neubiorev.2024.105548","container-title":"Neuroscience and biobehavioral reviews","abstract":"Mushrooms contain bioactive compounds with documented antioxidant and anti-inflammatory actions. Here, we present a systematic evaluation of epidemiological and clinical studies that investigate the role of mushrooms, either as a separate or integral dietary component, on neurocognition and mood. Following a search of four databases, a total of 34 human studies examining the effect of different mushrooms across varying age cohorts and health statuses were selected for inclusion. Epidemiological studies included in this review (n = 24) revealed a significant benefit of dietary patterns that included mushrooms of any species on cognition and mood in both healthy and compromised populations. However, the results obtained from intervention studies (n = 10) were mixed. Studies mainly investigated Lion's Mane (Hericium erinaceus), showing some enhancement of mood and cognitive function in middle-aged and older adults. Further acute and chronic human intervention studies are needed, using adequate sample sizes, employing appropriately sensitive neurocognitive tests, and investigating a range of dietary mushrooms, to confirm the effects of mushroom supplementation on neurocognition and mood in humans.Copyright © 2024 The Authors. Published by Elsevier Ltd.. All rights reserved.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Cha","given":"S.","literal":""},{"family":"Bell","given":"L.","literal":""},{"family":"Shukitt-Hale","given":"B.","literal":""},{"family":"Williams","given":"C. M.","literal":""}],"citation-key":"cha_review_2024","year":"2024","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["A review of the effects of mushrooms on mood and neurocognitive health across the lifespan."],"author-links":["[[Author/S. Cha]]","[[Author/L. Bell]]","[[Author/B. Shukitt-Hale]]","[[Author/C. M. Williams]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/cha_review_2024/cha_review_2024.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1q3wwyr","at":1774951889561}},"smart_blocks:Research/@cha_review_2024.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[0.02688908,-0.00002866,0.03050783,0.00146313,-0.00059905,0.07916996,0.03338988,-0.0000311,-0.03278477,0.0099129,-0.00498083,-0.04809958,0.03061747,0.03438082,-0.00188167,0.01659283,0.02472272,-0.01441909,-